 itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001085963"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=77ADAA02-5775-4A70-8B91-9DC9A54280AD&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fkevin-spacey-found-not-guilty-of-sexual-offenses-by-u-k-court-29c943cc&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Actor Kevin Spacey was found not guilty of sexual assault against four men by a UK court. Spacey was cleared of all the allegations against him involving the British men between 2001 and 2013, according to a court official. Photo: Andy Rain/Shutterstock<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001085963"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/humza-jilani" itemprop="url" rel="author">Humza Jilani</a></span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jennifer-calfas" itemprop="url" rel="author">Jennifer Calfas</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Updated July 26, 2023 11:43 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kevin-spacey-found-not-guilty-of-sexual-offenses-by-u-k-court-29c943cc"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> LONDON—Actor Kevin Spacey was found not guilty of sexual assault against four men by a UK court, closing out <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kevin-spacey-pleads-not-guilty-to-u-k-sexual-assault-charges-11673635720?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">a series of sexual misconduct trials</a> that have dogged the two-time Oscar winner for years.</p><p> Spacey was cleared by a jury of all the allegations against him involving the British men between 2001 and 2013, according to an official at Southwark Crown Court.</p><p> In a statement outside the court, Spacey said that he was humbled by the verdict.</p><p> “There&#39;s a lot for me to process after what has just happened today. But I would like to say that I&#39;m enormously grateful to the jury for having taken the time to examine all of the evidence and all of the facts, carefully, before they reached their decision,” Spacey said.</p><p> The period in question covered his time as artistic director of the Old Vic, a 200-year-old London theater, between 2003 and 2015.</p><p> Spacey, 63, had pleaded not guilty to all charges, ranging from indecent assault and sexual assault to causing a person to engage in penetrative sexual activity, which carries a maximum penalty of life in prison.</p><p> The verdict brings to an end a closely followed four-week trial, in which both sides focused heavily on Spacey&#39;s star power and name recognition. Spacey&#39;s lawyer depicted the actor as the victim of a trial by social media. Christine Agnew, the lead prosecutor, argued that the actor had abused his celebrity status to prey on young men. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823091?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Actor Kevin Spacey outside a UK court this week.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: PETER CZIBORRA/REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> The trial featured testimony from singer Elton John and his husband, David Furnish. One of the accusers alleged that Spacey had assaulted him on the way to one of the couple&#39;s white-tie galas in 2004 or 2005. John and Furnish said via video link that Spacey hadn&#39;t attended such an event during those years, the Associated Press reported.</p><p> Wednesday&#39;s verdict closes years of legal entanglements in which Spacey has faced multiple accusations of sexual misconduct in the US and the UK</p><p> In the UK, Spacey originally <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kevin-spacey-pleads-not-guilty-to-u-k-sexual-assault-charges-11657816622?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">faced four counts of sexual assault</a> and one count of “causing a person to engage in penetrative sexual activity without consent.” Those incidents were alleged to have taken place in London in 2005 and 2008, and in Gloucestershire in 2013, with victims who are now in their 30s and 40s.</p><p> British prosecutors <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kevin-spacey-pleads-not-guilty-to-u-k-sexual-assault-charges-11673635720?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">brought seven additional charges</a> against Spacey last year following an investigation by London&#39;s Metropolitan Police Service. Those charges included three counts of sexual assault, three counts of indecent assault and one count of causing a person to engage in sexual activity related to alleged assaults on a man between 2001 and 2004. Prosecutors didn&#39;t detail the alleged incidents nor name the man.</p><p> He was cleared of charges by a US court last year.</p><p> Spacey, who won Oscars for his roles in “The Usual Suspects” and “American Beauty,” was fired in 2017 from a starring role in</p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NFLX" class="">Netflix</a> <span class="company-name-type">&#39;s</span> “House of Cards,” after actor Anthony Rapp accused him of making a sexual advance in 1986 when Rapp was 14 and Spacey was an adult.<p></p><p> In New York, a federal jury found Spacey not liable in a battery claim brought by Rapp after <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kevin-spacey-found-not-liable-in-civil-sexual-misconduct-case-brought-by-rent-star-anthony-rapp-11666297697?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">a two-week civil trial</a> . The 11-person jury found Rapp, who starred in “Star Trek:Discovery,” didn&#39;t prove by a preponderance of evidence that Spacey “touched a sexual or intimate part or parts of Mr. Rapp.”</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/prosecutors-drop-case-against-kevin-spacey-11563397024?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">State prosecutors in Massachusetts in 2019</a> dropped a separate case against Spacey in which he was accused of groping a young man at a Nantucket bar. Spacey had denied the allegations and pleaded not guilty.</p><p> In an interview with a German newspaper before the UK proceedings began, Spacey insisted that he would return to acting after the trial.</p><p> “There are people right now who are ready to hire me the moment I am cleared of these charges,” ZeitMagazin quoted him as saying.</p><p> Write to Humza Jilani at <a href="mailto:humza.jilani@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">humza.jilani@wsj.com</a> and Jennifer Calfas at <a href="mailto:jennifer.calfas@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">jennifer.calfas@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 26 Jul 2023 15:43:00 GMT</pubDate><gu